9	16534	Sunshine has started to spill over the walls and furniture in my dorm room, and I finally wore a dress without tights today  spring (and Dillo weekend!) is officially here. Celebrate with some classic drinks, or get adventurous with twists on some warm weather favorites!\r\n<h3><b>The Original: Margarita</b></h3>\r\n<b></b>[freshman]\r\n\r\n<b>Total Time:</b>5 minutes\r\n\r\n<b>Servings: </b>1\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients:</b>\r\n1 shot silver (clear) tequila\r\n2/3 shot triple sec\r\n1/3 shot lime juice\r\nSplash of simple syrup (1 part sugar mixed with 1 part water)\r\nSalt (for rim of glass)\r\n\r\n<b>Directions:</b>\r\n1. Combine all ingredients with ice in a cocktail shaker and shake until cold.Or stir together vigorously in a cup.\r\n2. Strain into a glass with a salt rim.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_13512" align="aligncenter" width="676"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Margarita-1-1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-13512" alt="Photo by Hannah Lin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Margarita-1-1.jpg" width="676" height="1024" /></a> Photo by Hannah Lin[/caption]\r\n<h3><b>The Twist: Grapefruit Margarita</b></h3>\r\n[freshman]\r\n\r\n<b>Total Time:</b>5 minutes\r\n\r\n<b>Servings:</b>1\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients:</b>\r\n1 1/3 shots silver tequila\r\n2/3 shot triple sec\r\n1/3 shot lime juice\r\n5 1/3 shots grapefruit juice\r\nSalt (for rim of glass)\r\n\r\n<b>Directions:</b>\r\n1. Combine all ingredients with ice in a cocktail shaker and shake until cold. Or stir together vigorously in a cup.\r\n2. Strain into a glass with a salt rim.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_13518" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Margarita-2.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-13518" alt="Photo by Hannah Lin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Margarita-2.jpg" width="1024" height="641" /></a> Photo by Hannah Lin[/caption]\r\n<h3>The Original: Lemonade</h3>\r\n[freshman]\r\n\r\n<b>Total time: </b>10 minutes\r\n\r\n<b>Serving:</b>6\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients:</b>\r\n1 cup sugar\r\n5 cups water\r\n1 cup lemon juice\r\n\r\n<b>Directions:</b>\r\n1. Combine sugar and 1 cup of water in a small sauce pan.\r\n2. Bring it to a boil and stir to dissolve the sugar, forming a simple syrup. *To simplify, microwave sugar water mixture for 3-4 minutes, then stir again. Repeat process until sugar is dissolved and mixture is clear.*\r\n3. Allow simple syrup to cool to room temperature, then cover and refrigerate until cold.\r\n4. Stir together the chilled syrup, lemon juice and remaining 4 cups of water in a large pitcher and serve over ice.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_13514" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Lemonade-21.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-13514" alt="Photo by Hannah Lin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Lemonade-21.jpg" width="1024" height="675" /></a> Photo by Hannah Lin[/caption]\r\n<h3>The Twist: Lemonade-Mint Iced Tea</h3>\r\n[freshman]\r\n\r\n<b>Total Time: </b>25 minutes\r\n\r\n<b>Servings: </b>Makes about 12 cups\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients:</b>\r\n3 tablespoons crushed mint leaves\r\n4 cups boiled water\r\n cup instant iced tea powder\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n8 cups cold water\r\n1 6-ounce can frozen lemonade concentrate, thawed\r\n\r\n<b>Directions:</b>\r\n1. Combine mint leaves, boiling water, instant tea powder and sugar in a 1-gallon pitcher.\r\n2. Stir to dissolve sugar.\r\n3. Let stand for 15 minutes to cool.\r\n4. Stir in cold water and lemonade concentrate.\r\n5. Serve over ice in tall glasses.<b></b>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_13515" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Iced-Tea-Mint-11.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-13515" alt="Photo by Hannah Lin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Iced-Tea-Mint-11.jpg" width="1024" height="710" /></a> Photo by Hannah Lin[/caption]\r\n<h3>The Original: Unsweetened Iced Tea</h3>\r\n[freshman]\r\n\r\n<b>Total Time: </b>15 minutes\r\n\r\n<b>Servings: </b>Makes 8 cups\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients:</b>\r\n8 tea bags\r\n cup hot tap water\r\n7  cups cold water\r\n\r\n<b>Directions:</b>\r\n1. Place tea bags in a 2-quart (8-cup) pitcher.\r\n2. Add hot water to pitcher.\r\n3. Let the tea steep for 15 minutes.\r\n4. Add the cold water and remove tea bags.\r\n5. Refrigerate and serve over ice.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_13519" align="aligncenter" width="718"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Drinks-1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-13519" alt="Photo by Hannah Lin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Drinks-1.jpg" width="718" height="1024" /></a> Photo by Hannah Lin[/caption]\r\n<h3>The Twist: Spiked Boston Iced Tea</h3>\r\n[freshman]\r\n\r\n<b>Total Time: </b>35 minutes\r\n\r\n<b>Servings:</b>8\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients:</b>\r\n8 cups water\r\n1/2 cup white sugar\r\n8 tea bags\r\n1/2 12-ounce can frozen cranberry juice concentrate\r\n1 cup raspberry vodka\r\n\r\n<b>Directions</b>\r\n1. Place water in large pot and heat on high until it boils.\r\n2. Add sugar to water and stir until dissolved.\r\n3. Add tea bags and steep until the tea is as strong as you like steep longer for stronger tea, or steep shorter for weaker.\r\n4. Stir in cranberry concentrate and allow to cool.\r\n5. Stir in raspberry vodka.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_13516" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Iced-Tea-1-1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-13516" alt="Photo by Hannah Lin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Iced-Tea-1-1.jpg" width="1024" height="744" /></a> Photo by Hannah Lin[/caption]	Dillo Weekend: Drink Your Way into Spring!	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/dillo-weekend-drink-your-way-into-spring/	\N	20