12	16599	Ramen is the classic college student food staple, but after endless nights with those Cup Noodles, they start to lose their appeal. Here are a couple of ways to spice up the dozens of ramen noodle packets stuffed in your drawers.\r\n<h3>Ramen Noodle Soup</h3>\r\nThis ramen soup allows you to really play with the recipe. I chose to use edamame, because it's convenient to pick up at the C-store, but you can also use sugar snap peas, scallions or whatever vegetable suits you. Also, if you don't have cayenne pepper, try using sriracha sauce or another hot sauce to enhance the flavor.\r\n\r\n[freshman]\r\n\r\n<b>Total Time:</b> 5 minutes\r\n\r\n<b>Servings:</b> 1\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients:</b>\r\n1 packet of ramen noodles (any flavor)\r\n1 egg\r\n1/2 cup of desired vegetable\r\nCayenne pepper (or any flavor enhancer)\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n1. Cook the raw noodles following instructions on packaging.\r\n2. Once the noodles are finished cooking, add the packet of seasoning.\r\n3. Add egg to the cooked noodles and water, and stir until egg is cooked and broken up.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_12671" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-1-Egg1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-12671" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-1-Egg1.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Justin Shannin[/caption]\r\n\r\n4. Pour into bowl.\r\n5. Fold in the vegetable of your choice.\r\n6. Mix in cayenne pepper, or flavor enhancer of your choice.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_12670" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-1-Final-21.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-12670" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-1-Final-21.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Justin Shannin[/caption]\r\n<h3><b>Ramen Stir-Fry</b></h3>\r\nThis recipe has similar ingredients to the one above, but this cooking method makes it more reminiscent of a stir-fry or fried rice dish.\r\n\r\nSpoon University is a content-sharing network of student publications on campuses nationwide focused on eating in college.\r\n\r\n[freshman]\r\n\r\n<b>Total Time:</b> 7 minutes\r\n\r\n<b>Servings:</b> 1\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients:</b>\r\n1 packet of ramen noodles (any flavor)\r\n1 egg\r\n1/2 cup of desired vegetable\r\nCayenne pepper (or any flavor enhancer)\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n1. Cook the raw noodles following instructions on packaging.\r\n2. Break egg into small bowl and stir with a whisk or fork.\r\n3. Pour stirred egg in skillet on medium heat and scramble.\r\n4. Drain water from noodles.\r\n5. Add packet of seasoning to noodles.\r\n5. Fold scrambled egg into mixture.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_12665" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-2-Egg-Pouring.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-12665" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-2-Egg-Pouring.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Justin Shannin[/caption]\r\n\r\n6. Add vegetables.\r\n7. Add flavor enhancer.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_12662" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-2-Final.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-12662" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-2-Final.jpg" width="1024" height="708" /></a> Photo by Justin Shannin[/caption]\r\n<h3><b>Eggs, Bacon, and Noodle Scramble</b></h3>\r\nThis is a breakfast ramen recipe, designed to hearty up your basic scrambled eggs and use up those extra packets of ramen.\r\n\r\n[freshman]\r\n\r\n<strong>Total time:</strong> 15 minutes\r\n\r\n<strong>Servings:</strong> 1-2\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n1 packet of ramen noodles\r\n2 eggs\r\n1/4 cup cheddar cheese\r\n1 tablespoon butter\r\n2 strips bacon\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_12674" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ingredients1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-12674" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ingredients1.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Justin Shannin[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n1. Break up the raw noodles and cook normally.\r\n2. When noodles are cooked, set aside (do not add seasoning packet).\r\n3. Break eggs into small bowl and stir with a whisk or fork.\r\n4. Cook the strips of bacon and set aside.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_12660" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-3-Bacon-Pieces1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-12660" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-3-Bacon-Pieces1.jpg" width="1024" height="589" /></a> Photo by Justin Shannin[/caption]\r\n\r\n5. Pour out all but 1 tablespoon of bacon fat from the skillet.\r\n6. Put 1 tablespoon of butter in the skillet with the bacon fat.\r\n7. Add the cooked noodles to the skillet and stir.\r\n8. Add in the whisked eggs and stir/scramble.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_12677" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-3-Pouring-in-Egg1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-12677" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-3-Pouring-in-Egg1.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Justin Shannin[/caption]\r\n\r\n9. Slowly add in cheddar cheese (more or less for desired taste).\r\n10. When finished, pour onto dish and crumble cooked bacon on top.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_12679" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-3-Final1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-12679" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ramen-3-Final1.jpg" width="1024" height="643" /></a> Photo by Justin Shannin[/caption]	Spice Up Your Ramen	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/spice-up-your-ramen/	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:27.833197	2014-01-14 18:55:27.833197	:</b>\r\n1 packet of ramen noodles (any flavor)\r\n1 egg\r\n1/2 cup of desired vegetable\r\nCayenne pepper (or any flavor enhancer)\r\n\r\n<strong>
