102	18406	In the process of weaning myself off of following recipes, Ive been thinking a lot about flavor combinations. Last week I was staring into my fridge, wondering what I was going to make for dinner when I remembered I had just bought some bacon. Yes, sometimes it is okay to shape your entire meal around bacon. You can accuse me of stress eating, but the first thing I thought after bacon was Mac n cheese. (Hey, finals week was stressful!) In an attempt to salvage this meal from becoming a heart attack in a bowl, I spotted asparagus and onions and knew theyd fit well. And spoiler alert: there's no cheese in this recipe. Surprisingly enough, mashed sweet potato and nutritional yeast come together to form a creamy sauce thats fresher, more flavorful and certainly healthier than your average cheese sauce.<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n[medium]\r\n\r\n<strong>Prep Time</strong>: 10 minutes\r\n<strong>Cook Time</strong>: 35 minutes\r\n<strong>Total Time</strong>: 45 minutes\r\n\r\n<strong>Servings</strong>: 6\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n6-7 tablespoons nutritional yeast flakes (not the same as regular yeast!)\r\n1  cups plain milk (any kind- 2%, almond, soy, etc.)\r\n1  teaspoons lemon juice\r\nSalt, to taste\r\n1 large or 2 small sweet potatoes, about 1 cup mashed\r\n1 teaspoon black pepper\r\n onion, chopped\r\n4-5 pieces of bacon, diced\r\n1 clove garlic, minced\r\n1 bunch asparagus, chopped\r\n8 oz. pasta\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n1. Fill a medium-sized saucepan with water (until it reaches about two inches from the top) and bring to a boil.\r\n2. While water is heating up, peel and chop sweet potatoes into cubes.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_7191" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sweet-potato-bacon-mac-n-cheese/sweetpotatomac02peelingpotato2/" rel="attachment wp-att-7191"><img class="size-large wp-image-7191" alt="Photo by Kelda Baljon" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2012/12/SweetPotatoMac02PeelingPotato2-1024x685.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Kelda Baljon[/caption]\r\n\r\n3. Once water is boiling, add sweet potato chunks.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_7192" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sweet-potato-bacon-mac-n-cheese/sweetpotatomac06boilingpotatoes/" rel="attachment wp-att-7192"><img class="size-large wp-image-7192" alt="Photo by Kelda Baljon" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2012/12/SweetPotatoMac06BoilingPotatoes-1024x685.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Kelda Baljon[/caption]\r\n\r\n4. Cook sweet potato for about 20 minutes, or until tender. When the sweet potatoes are done, mash with a fork or potato masher until smooth.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_7197" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sweet-potato-bacon-mac-n-cheese/sweetpotatomac13cupofpotatolight/" rel="attachment wp-att-7197"><img class="size-large wp-image-7197" alt="Photo by Kelda Baljon" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2012/12/SweetPotatoMac13CupofPotatoLight-1024x685.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Kelda Baljon[/caption]\r\n\r\n5. While the sweet potatoes are cooking, sautchopped bacon in a large pan until crispy.\r\n6. Using a spatula or spoon, move bacon pieces to a plate covered with a paper towels to absorb the grease. Do not drain bacon grease from the pan, and keep the burner on.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_7196" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sweet-potato-bacon-mac-n-cheese/sweetpotatomac08baconontowel/" rel="attachment wp-att-7196"><img class="size-large wp-image-7196" alt="Photo by Kelda Baljon" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2012/12/SweetPotatoMac08BacononTowel-1024x685.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Kelda Baljon[/caption]\r\n\r\n7. Sautchopped asparagus, onion and garlic in pan with the bacon grease. Cook until onions are tender and translucent, about 5-7 minutes.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_7195" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sweet-potato-bacon-mac-n-cheese/sweetpotatomac09-jpgsauteedveggies2/" rel="attachment wp-att-7195"><img class="size-large wp-image-7195" alt="Photo by Kelda Baljon" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2012/12/SweetPotatoMac09.jpgSauteedVeggies2-1024x685.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Kelda Baljon[/caption]\r\n\r\n8. In a medium-sized saucepan, bring 4-6 cups of water to a boil. Add pasta and cook until al dente.\r\n9. In a large bowl, combine nutritional yeast, milk, lemon juice, salt, pepper and 1 cup of mashed sweet potatoes until smooth.\r\n10. When pasta is cooked, strain water and transfer pasta to the large bowl with the sauce.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_7198" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sweet-potato-bacon-mac-n-cheese/sweetpotatomac15altogether/" rel="attachment wp-att-7198"><img class="size-large wp-image-7198" alt="Photo by Kelda Baljon" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2012/12/SweetPotatoMac15Altogether-1024x685.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Kelda Baljon[/caption]\r\n\r\n11. Add sauted veggies, toss and serve.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_7199" align="aligncenter" width="685"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sweet-potato-bacon-mac-n-cheese/sweetpotatomac22final7vertical/" rel="attachment wp-att-7199"><img class="size-large wp-image-7199" alt="Photo by Kelda Baljon" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2012/12/SweetPotatoMac22Final7Vertical-685x1024.jpg" width="685" height="1024" /></a> Photo by Kelda Baljon[/caption]	Sweet Potato Bacon Mac 'n' Cheese	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/sweet-potato-bacon-mac-n-cheese/	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:29.149763	2014-01-14 18:55:29.149763	:</strong>\r\n6-7 tablespoo