alkema" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/P10199751.jpg" width="1024" height="768" /> Photo by Kendra Valkema[/caption]\r\n\r\n8. Sprinkle with cheese. Do not stir or whisk in cheese.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_12241" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img class="size-full wp-image-12241" alt="Photo by Kendra Valkema" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/P1019977.jpg" width="1024" height="768" /> Photo by Kendra Valkema[/caption]\r\n\r\n9. Cover and let cook for about 15 minutes or until eggs have set and cheese is melted.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_12240" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img class="size-full wp-image-12240" alt="Photo by Kendra Valkema" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/P10199781.jpg" width="1024" height="768" /> Photo by Kendra Valkema[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_12239" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img class="size-full wp-image-12239" alt="Photo by Kendra Valkema" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/05/P10199801.jpg" width="1024" height="768" /> Photo by Kendra Valkema[/caption]	Sunday Side Up: Stove Top Frittata	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/sunday-side-up-stove-top-frittata/	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:28.161983	2014-01-14 18:55:28.161983	</strong>:\r\n1 large onion\r\n2 cloves garlic\r\n1 tablespoon olive oil\r\n1 green bell pepper\r\n1 tomato, seeds removed\r\n1 large handful spinach\r\n6 eggs\r\n1/2 cup milk\r\n1 large handful shredded cheese\r\n\r\n<strong>
