70	17357	On a lazy winter weekend, you probably want to avoid facing your daunting amount of homework and procrastinate by laying in bed and eating something warm and sweet. Monkey bread is an ooey-gooey, cinnamon-sugar, pull-apart concoction that will get you up and running, or glued you to your bed in a caramelized haze. Made from Pillsbury Grands! biscuits, this is a simple college brunch, or paired with a scoop of ice cream, makes for a wonderful dessert as well.\r\n\r\n[freshman]\r\n\r\n<strong>Prep Time:</strong> 10 minutes\r\n<strong>Cook Time:</strong> 20 minutes\r\n<strong>Total Time:</strong> 30 minutes\r\n\r\n<strong>Servings:</strong>5\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n2 cans Pillsbury Grands! Biscuits\r\n1/2 cup sugar\r\n1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\r\n3/4 cup butter\r\n1 cup firmly packed brown sugar\r\n1/2 cup of pecans or other nuts (optional)\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n1. Preheat oven to 350F.\r\n2. Pop open the biscuit cans and cut each individual biscuit into four parts.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_8461" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sunday-side-up-monkey-bread/dough-cutting/" rel="attachment wp-att-8461"><img class="size-full wp-image-8461" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/02/Dough-Cutting.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Justin Shannin[/caption]\r\n\r\n3. Pour sugar and cinnamon into a large Ziploc bag and shake to mix.\r\n4. Add biscuit pieces into the Ziploc bag of cinnamon sugar, seal the bag and shake until all pieces are covered with cinnamon sugary goodness.\r\n5. Melt butter in a small bowl and mix in brown sugar for a thick glaze.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_8468" align="aligncenter" width="959"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sunday-side-up-monkey-bread/mixing_1/" rel="attachment wp-att-8468"><img class="size-full wp-image-8468" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/02/Mixing_1.jpg" width="959" height="768" /></a> Photo by Justin Shannin[/caption]\r\n\r\n6. Put cinnamon sugar-coated biscuit pieces in any deep pan. Do not use a sheet pan.\r\n*If you chose to add nuts, sprinkle them in here with the dough pieces.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_8464" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sunday-side-up-monkey-bread/sugar-pouring-on-dough/" rel="attachment wp-att-8464"><img class="size-full wp-image-8464" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/02/Sugar-Pouring-on-Dough.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Justin Shannin[/caption]\r\n\r\n7. Evenly pour glaze over dough.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_8472" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sunday-side-up-monkey-bread/mix-pouring/" rel="attachment wp-att-8472"><img class="size-full wp-image-8472" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/02/Mix-Pouring.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Justin Shannin[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_8470" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sunday-side-up-monkey-bread/mix-settled_2/" rel="attachment wp-att-8470"><img class="size-full wp-image-8470" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/02/Mix-Settled_2.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Justin Shannin[/caption]\r\n\r\n8. Bake for twenty minutes.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_8463" align="aligncenter" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sunday-side-up-monkey-bread/final-product-pulling-apart/" rel="attachment wp-att-8463"><img class="size-full wp-image-8463" alt="Photo by Justin Shannin" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/02/Final-Product-Pulling-Apart.jpg" width="1024" height="685" /></a> Photo by Jus