ght="211" /> Photo by Justin Shannin.[/caption]	Bite-Sized Fruit Treats	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/bite-sized-fruit-treats-2/	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:29.038382	2014-01-14 18:55:29.038382	\N
90	18173	Confession: I am a carb-addict. Rice, noodles, bread, cakes  whatever it is, I could never give it up. But what really tears my self-control apart are potatoes. I love them in every way: fried, baked, steamed, roasted or mashed. Most of my original recipes involve potatoes as the main ingredient so Im always looking for a good potato recipe.\r\n\r\nWhen I came across this recipe for tater tot nachos a.k.a. totchos, I had to make it. Totchos are extremely easy to make since most of the cooking involves assembling the pile of toppings on top of the crispy tater tots.\r\n\r\nYou can also play around with your choice of toppings. Instead of bacon, you can opt for chorizo or lean ground beef cooked with chili powder. If you are vegetarian, roasted bell pepper slices go very well with cheese and the crispy potato. For extra heat, you can add pickled jalapeo or some sriracha on top of the tater tots. I personally like to top my totchos with a sunny side up egg. The possibilities are endless!\r\n\r\nThis is a great dish to munch on while watching the Super Bowl this weekend. Word of caution: a fork is advised since eating totchos can get messy.\r\n\r\nWatch the video below to see exactly how I made tater tot nachos and click here to see how I made the <a title="How to Make Pico de Gallo" href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/how-to-make-pico-de-gallo/"><strong>pico de gallo</strong></a>.\r\n\r\n[easy]\r\n\r\n<b>Prep Time: </b>5 minutes<b></b>\r\n<b>Cook Time: </b>30  35 minutes (depending on the<b> </b>tater tots brand)\r\n<b>Total Time: </b>35  40 minutes\r\n\r\n<b>Serves: </b>3-4 people\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients: </b>\r\n1/2 bag of Tater Tots\r\nBlock of cheese (I used pepper jack, but you can also go with sharp white cheddar, mozzarella or any cheese of your choice. I didnt specify the amount because you can put as much or as little as you want! You can also use premade salsa con queso).\r\n2 pieces of bacon\r\nSour cream\r\nGuacamole\r\nPico de gallo\r\nA few green onions to garnish\r\n\r\n<b>Directions:</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">1. Preheat the oven according to the instructions on the tater tot bag.</span>\r\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">2. Cover the pan with foil and spread tater tots evenly on the pan.</span>\r\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">3. Bake tater tots until golden brown.</span>\r\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">4. While the tater tots are baking, dice the bacon into bite-sized pieces.</span>\r\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">5. Fry the bacon pieces until they are crispy.</span>\r\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">6. When the tater tots are done, load them into a glass or ceramic bowl.</span>\r\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">7. Top the tater tots with a generous amount of cheese and bake them in the oven until the cheese is bubbly.</span>\r\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">8. Top that with bacon pieces, pico de gallo, guacamole and sour cream.</span>\r\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">9. Add a few sliced green onions on top to garnish.</span>\r\n\r\n<i>A huge thanks to Andrea Kang for helping make this dish.</i>	How to Make Tater Tot Nachos	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/how-to-make-tater-tot-nachos/	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:29.042754	2014-01-14 18:55:29.042754	: </b>\r\n1/2 bag of Tater Tots\r\nBlock of cheese (I used pepper jack, but you can also go with sharp white cheddar, mozzarella or any cheese of your choice. I didnt specify the amount because you can put as much or as little as you want! You can also use premade salsa con queso).\r\n2 pieces of bacon\r\nSour cream\r\nGuacamole\r\nPico de gallo\r\nA few green onions to garnish\r\n\r\n<b>
