tly browned.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_7716" align="aligncenter" width="1280"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/bacon-chocolate-chip-cookies/baconchocchipcookies07cookiesbakedall/" rel="attachment wp-att-7716"><img class="size-full wp-image-7716" alt="BaconChocChipCookies07CookiesBakedAll" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/01/BaconChocChipCookies07CookiesBakedAll.jpg" width="1280" height="853" /></a> Photo by Kelda Baljon[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_7718" align="aligncenter" width="1280"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/bacon-chocolate-chip-cookies/baconchocchipcookies13final3/" rel="attachment wp-att-7718"><img class="size-full wp-image-7718" alt="Photo by Kelda Baljon" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/01/BaconChocChipCookies13Final3.jpg" width="1280" height="853" /></a> Photo by Kelda Baljon[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;	Bacon Chocolate Chip Cookies	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/bacon-chocolate-chip-cookies/	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:29.105328	2014-01-14 18:55:29.105328	:</b>\r\n2 cups almond flour\r\n1/4 teaspoon baking soda\r\n1/4 teaspoon salt\r\n4-5 strips bacon\r\n1/4 cup chocolate chips\r\n1/3 cup coconut oil\r\n1/4 cup maple syrup\r\n1 tablespoon vanilla\r\n1 tablespoon milk (I used almond milk, but any milk will do)\r\n\r\n<b>
