l glaze thickens.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_7288" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/sunday-side-up-pumpkin-donuts/pdglaze/" rel="attachment wp-att-7288"><img class="size-full wp-image-7288" alt="Photo by Andrea Kang" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/01/PDGlaze.jpg" width="1024" height="1536" /></a> Photo by Andrea Kang[/caption]\r\n\r\n17. Using a rubber spatula, scoop frosting onto donut.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_7290" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img class="size-full wp-image-7290" alt="Photo by Andrea Kang" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/01/PDGlazeSpatula.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /> Photo by Andrea Kang[/caption]\r\n\r\n18. Return donut to cooling rack and let frosting harden.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_7289" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img class="size-full wp-image-7289" alt="Photo by Andrea Kang" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/01/PDGlazedCoolingRack2.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /> Photo by Andrea Kang[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_7291" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img class="size-full wp-image-7291" alt="Photo by Andrea Kang" src="http://nu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/01/PDFinal2.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /> Photo by Andrea Kang[/caption]	Glazed Pumpkin Donuts	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/glazed-pumpkin-donuts/	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:29.139678	2014-01-14 18:55:29.139678	:</b>\r\n2 tablespoons butter or butter substitute\r\n1/2 cup + 1 tablespoon sugar, divided\r\n1/2 cup pumpkin puree\r\n1/3 cup yogurt\r\n1 egg\r\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\r\n2 cups gluten-free or all-purpose flour\r\n2 teaspoons baking powder\r\n1/2 teaspoon baking soda\r\n2 teaspoons cinnamon, divided\r\n1 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice (or  teaspoon ginger +  teaspoon nutmeg)\r\n1/2 teaspoon salt\r\n1 cup confectioner's sugar\r\nWater\r\n\r\n<b>
