es you have on hand)\r\n<em> </em>medium yellow onion\r\n1 clove garlic\r\n1 tablespoon butter, plus a bit more for frying\r\n<strong>Optional:</strong>  cup fresh herbs like parsley or chives\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n1. Minceonion and garlic.\r\n2. Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a medium-sized skillet. Saut onion for 5 minutes over medium heat until translucent. Add garlic and saut for an additional 35 minutes. Remove from heat.\r\n3. Stir together onion and garlic, leftover mashed potatoes, Parmesan cheese, chopped leftover vegetables, flour and fresh herbs in a separate bowl.\r\n4. Melt a bit of butter in the skillet over medium heat. Shape  cup-sized balls of the potato mixture into -inch thick patties. Fry each patty until golden brown on each side, about 34 minutes each. Serve immediately.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;	Potatoes Four Ways	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/potatoes-four-ways/	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:29.194586	2014-01-14 18:55:29.194586	:</strong>\r\n2 pounds<em> </em>medium-sized Yukon Gold potatoes\r\n1/3 cup olive oil\r\n2 tablespoons butter\r\n6 cloves garlic, peeled and halved\r\nSalt and black pepper to taste\r\n\r\n<strong>
