182	19815	Oatmeal is one of those foods that college students love to hate: its quick, easy, and cheap, yet often lacks flavor. Luckily, oatmeal is something thats easily spiced up. Although Im notorious for dressing my oats with calorie-laden chocolate chips or brown sugar, there are healthy additives that taste just as sweet and have the nutritional value to keep you energized. This crunchy oatmeal recipe takes only five minutes - so cut time from your morning breakfast routine and I promise, it'll have even the biggest oatmeal hater falling in love.\r\n\r\n[easy]\r\n\r\n<strong>Prep Time:</strong> 5 minutes\r\n<strong>Cook Time:</strong> 1 minute\r\n<strong>Total Time:</strong> 6 minutes\r\n\r\n<strong>Servings:</strong> 1\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n cup old-fashioned oats\r\n2 spoonfuls of Greek yogurt, any flavor\r\n1-tablespoon peanut butter\r\n cup Kashi GoLean Crunch (or your favorite crunchy cereal)\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://michigan.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/8/2013/10/10127826936_6940e43bea_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-490" alt="Photo by Annie Madole" src="http://michigan.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/8/2013/10/10127826936_6940e43bea_b.jpg" width="1024" height="680" /></a> Photo by Annie Madole[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n\t<li>Prepare the oats with one cup of water and microwave on high for 90 seconds.</li>\r\n\t<li>Spoon in two dollops of your favorite Greek yogurt and mix thoroughly.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img class="size-full wp-image-491" alt="Photo by Annie Madole" src="http://michigan.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/8/2013/10/10127914883_1c887b72c7_b.jpg" width="1024" height="680" /> Photo by Annie Madole[/caption]</li>\r\n\t<li>Reheat the mixture in the microwave for fifteen seconds, or until warm.</li>\r\n\t<li>Stir in one tablespoon of peanut butter.</li>\