t/uploads/sites/3/2013/10/10259991133_e122232abb_b.jpg" width="770" height="554" /></a> Photo by Molly Krohe[/caption]\r\n\r\n4. Mix until everything is properly blended\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="aligncenter" width="770"]<a href="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/10/10259780954_3f4669493d_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-207" alt="Photo by Molly Krohe" src="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/10/10259780954_3f4669493d_b.jpg" width="770" height="634" /></a> Photo by Molly Krohe[/caption]\r\n\r\n5. Make small 2 inch circles of dough and place them on a cookie sheet\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="aligncenter" width="770"]<a href="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/10/10259881986_a5481718e9_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-208" alt="Photo by Molly Krohe" src="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/10/10259881986_a5481718e9_b.jpg" width="770" height="501" /></a> Photo by Molly Krohe[/caption]\r\n\r\n6. Place in the oven for about 12 minutes\r\n\r\n7. When they are starting to get firm on the bottom, remove from oven and let cool (or just dig in!)\r\n\r\n<a href="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/10/10259987963_f36e06c9e2_b.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-206" alt="10259987963_f36e06c9e2_b" src="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/10/10259987963_f36e06c9e2_b.jpg" width="770" height="518" /></a>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="aligncenter" width="770"]<a href="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/10/10259879996_2e374b1062_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-212" alt="Photo by Molly Krohe" src="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/10/10259879996_2e374b1062_b.jpg" width="770" height="508" /></a> Photo by Molly Krohe[/caption]	Gluten-Free Sugar Cookies	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/?p=20494	\N	