lus calories without any health benefits?\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Clean-Eating-Sweet-Potato-Chips-3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-21452" alt=" Sweet Potato3" src="http://spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Clean-Eating-Sweet-Potato-Chips-3-1024x764.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a></p>\r\n5. Cook the sweet potatoes for 15-20 minutes in the oven while watching them to make sure they do not burn. You should take out the sweet potatoes once they start to have little brown specks on the top like the picture above (perfecto!).\r\n6. Use a spatula to transfer the sweet potato bits into a bowl while they are still hot, and shake cinnamon over them. Once they have cooled for about 5 minutes, drizzle honey over the top.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Sweet-Potato-Chips-with-Cinnamon.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-21117" alt="Sweet-Potato-Chips-with-Cinnamon" src="http://spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Sweet-Potato-Chips-with-Cinnamon.jpg" width="788" height="463" /></a>\r\n7. Eat and enjoy the savory sweet potatoes!\r\n\r\nLooks like I know what I'm making for dessert tonight. Who wants to join me?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;	Savory Sweet Potatoes	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/?p=20958	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:30.193879	2014-01-14 18:55:30.193879	:</strong>\r\n1 sweet potato (big or small depending on how hungry you are)\r\n3 tablespoons of olive oil or coconut oil\r\n2 dashes of cinnamon\r\nHoney\r\n\r\n<strong>
