icker bread pudding)\r\n3 large eggs\r\n1 cup milk\r\ncup sugar\r\n1 teaspoon vanilla\r\nDash of nutmeg\r\nDash of cinnamon\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a href="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/10/IMG_0385.jpg"><img class=" " alt="IMG_0385" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/10/IMG_0385.jpg" width="770" height="577" /></a> Photo by Vinita Saggurti[/caption]\r\n\r\n<b>
200	21290	With Halloween right around the corner, pumpkins are widely available. If you make a Jack-o-lanter, dont toss out the seeds when you clean your pumpkin! Roasted pumpkin seeds are a tasty (and versatile) snack. You can buy them in stores, buy it's much cheaper to make them yourself if you're already planning on cutting up a pumpkin. Here are five ways to dress up the simple fall seed, which are perfect for a bite between classes or to serve at your Halloween party.The measurements of the spices are approximate and can be adjusted to taste.\r\n<h2><strong>Simple Roasted Pumpkin Seeds</strong></h2>\r\n[easy]\r\n\r\n<b>Prep Time: </b>15 minutes\r\n<b>Cook Time: </b>10 minutes\r\n<b>Total Time: </b>25 minutes\r\n\r\n<b>Servings: </b>About 1 cup of seeds<b></b>\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients:\r\n</b>Seeds from 1 pumpkin\r\n2 tablespoons butter\r\nSalt to taste\r\n\r\n<b>Directions:\r\n</b>1. Preheat oven to 350F. Remove seeds from pumpkin and place them in a large bowl.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="980"]<a href="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/pumpkin-carve-1.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3631" alt="Photo by Tallie Gabriel" src="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/pumpkin-carve-1-1024x682.jpg" width="980" height="652" /></a> Photo by Tallie Gabriel[/caption]\r\n\r\n2. Fill the bowl with warm water and let rest for 5 minutes. This will loosen any bits of pumpkin from the seeds.\r\n3. Pour the seeds and water through a strainer. Dispose of any remaining pumpkin clumps.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="980"]<a href="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/strained-seeds-1.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3635" alt="Photo by Tallie Gabriel" src="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/strained-seeds-1-1024x682.jpg" width="980" height="652" /></a> Photo by Tallie Gabriel[/caption]\r\n\r\n4. Pour the pumpkin seeds onto a paper towel and dab them dry.\r\n5. Move the seeds onto a baking pan and spread them evenly. Melt butter in a microwave for about 20 seconds.\r\n6. Drizzle the butter over the seeds.\r\n7. Cook the seeds in the oven for 5-10 minutes or until they start to look golden brown. Remove and let cool.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="980"]<a href="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/toasted-seeds-1.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3637" alt="Photo by Tallie Gabriel" src="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/toasted-seeds-1-1024x682.jpg" width="980" height="652" /></a> Photo by Tallie Gabriel[/caption]\r\n\r\n8. Top with a sprinkling of salt.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Ginger Orange Roasted Pumpkin Seeds</strong></h2>\r\n<b>Ingredients:</b>\r\nSeeds from 1 pumpkin\r\n2 tablespoons butter\r\n1 teaspoon ground ginger\r\n1/2 tablespoon orange zest\r\n1 tablespoon sugar\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="682"]<a href="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/Sugar-and-spices-1.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3636" alt="Photo by Tallie Gabriel" src="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/Sugar-and-spices-1-682x1024.jpg" width="682" height="1024" /></a> Photo by Tallie Gabriel[/caption]\r\n\r\n<b>Directions:\r\n</b>1. Preheat oven to 350F. Remove seeds from pumpkin and place them in a large bowl.\r\n2. Fill the bowl with warm water and let rest for 5 minutes. This will loosen any bits of pumpkin from the seeds.\r\n3. Pour the seeds and water through a strainer. Dispose of any remaining pumpkin clumps.\r\n4. Pour the pumpkin seeds onto a paper towel and dab them dry.\r\n5. Melt butter in a microwave for about 20 seconds.\r\n6. Put the butter, ginger, orange zest and sugar into a plastic bag. Add pumpkin seeds to bag.\r\n7. Shake bag until seeds are coated evenly.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="980"]<a href="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/seeds-in-seasoning-bag-1.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3633" alt="Photo by Tallie Gabriel" src="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/seeds-in-seasoning-bag-1-1024x682.jpg" width="980" height="652" /></a> Photo by Tallie Gabriel[/caption]\r\n\r\n8. Move the seeds to a baking pan and spread them evenly.\r\n9. Cook the seeds in the oven for 5-10 minutes or until they start to look golden brown. Remove and let cool.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Pumpkin Pie Flavored Roasted Pumpkin Seeds</strong></h2>\r\n<b>Ingredients:\r\n</b>Seeds from 1 pumpkin\r\n2 tablespoons butter\r\n2 tablespoons cinnamon sugar\r\n1 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="980"]<a href="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/cinnamon-and-pumpkin-spice-1.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3627" alt="Photo by Tallie Gabriel" src="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/cinnamon-and-pumpkin-spice-1-1024x682.jpg" width="980" height="652" /></a> Photo by Tallie Gabriel[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n1. Preheat oven to 350F. Remove seeds from pumpkin and place them in a large bowl.\r\n2. Fill the bowl with warm water and let rest for 5 minutes. This will loosen any bits of pumpkin from the seeds.\r\n3. Pour the seeds and water through a strainer. Dispose of any remaining pumpkin clumps.\r\n4. Pour the pumpkin seeds onto a paper towel and dab them dry.\r\n5. Melt butter in a microwave for about 20 seconds.\r\n6. Put the butter, cinnamon sugar and pumpkin pie spice into a plastic bag. Add pumpkin seeds to bag.\r\n7. Shake bag until seeds are coated evenly.\r\n8. Move the seeds to a baking pan and spread them evenly.\r\n9. Cook the seeds in the oven for 5-10 minutes or until they start to look golden brown. Remove and let cool.\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2