="880" /></a> Photo by Tallie Gabriel[/caption]\r\n\r\n<b>Directions:</b>\r\n1. Preheat oven to 350F. Remove seeds from pumpkin and place them in a large bowl.\r\n2. Fill the bowl with warm water and let rest for 5 minutes. This will loosen any bits of pumpkin from the seeds.\r\n3. Pour the seeds and water through a strainer. Dispose of any remaining pumpkin clumps.\r\n4. Pour the pumpkin seeds onto a paper towel and dab them dry.\r\n5. Melt butter in a microwave for about 20 seconds.\r\n6. Put the butter, cheese, garlic powder and pepper into a plastic bag. Add pumpkin seeds to bag.\r\n7. Shake bag until seeds are coated evenly.\r\n8. Move the seeds to a baking pan and spread them evenly.\r\n9. Cook the seeds in the oven for 5-10 minutes or until they start to look golden brown. Remove and let cool.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="980"]<a href="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/finished-plates-of-seeds-1.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-3628" alt="Photo by Tallie Gabriel" src="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/10/finished-plates-of-seeds-1-1024x682.jpg" width="980" height="652" /></a> Photo by Tallie Gabriel[/caption]	1 Food, 5 Ways: Roasted Pumpkin Seeds	http://spoonuniversity.com/?post_type=recipe&#038;p=21290	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:30.344921	2014-01-14 18:55:30.344921	:\r\n</b>Seeds from 1 pumpkin\r\n2 tablespoons butter\r\nSalt to taste\r\n\r\n<b>
