095_80366d184d_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /></a> Photo by Raissa Xie[/caption]\r\n\r\n6. Squeeze lime into 1 cup of olive oil and whisk the liquid. Pour the diced tomatoes, onion, bell pepper, jalapeo andgarlic into the cup to create a salsa. Stir everything together.\r\n7. Coat the bottom of a shallow pan with olive oil. Pour the salsa onto the pan and saut on a burner for 10 minutes. Shake the pan once in a while to make sure every vegetable is cooked evenly.\r\n8. Place the chicken breast (thawed, if you used a frozen one) in another pan coated in olive oil. Sprinkle garlic powder, salt, and pepper on both sides of the chicken.\r\n9. Pan-fry the chicken on a medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes on each side. You can make sure its fully cooked by cutting into the chicken and seeing if the meat has turned white.\r\n10. Cut the chicken into small strips and place them into your serving bowl.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/10/10528826196_c1a8661d48_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-207" alt="Photo by Raissa Xie" src="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/10/10528826196_c1a8661d48_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /></a> Photo by Raissa Xie[/caption]\r\n\r\n11. Pour your now sautedsalsa on top and mix everything together. Add a tablespoon of sour cream if you're anything like me.\r\n12. Get out your tortilla chips and start double dipping.	Taco Salad with Homemade Salsa	http://spoonuniversity.com/?post_type=recipe&#038;p=21977	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:30.764901	2014-01-14 18:55:30.764901	:</strong>\r\n1 chicken breast\r\n1 teaspoon garlic powder\r\n1 teaspoon salt\r\n1 teaspoon black pepper\r\n head romaine lettuce\r\n2 cups frozen corn\r\n1 avocado\r\n1 cup olive oil\r\n lime\r\n1 tomato\r\n red onion\r\n1 red bell pepper\r\n1/2jalapeo\r\n1 garlic clove\r\n1 tablespoon sour cream\r\nA handful of your favorite tortilla chips\r\n\r\n<str