ula to separate any attached cookies. Let them cool slightly and serve warm.<em>\r\n</em>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/10810909286_9f6419dc90_b.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-343" alt="10810909286_9f6419dc90_b" src="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/10810909286_9f6419dc90_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /></a>	Ooey Gooey Marshmallow Cookies	http://spoonuniversity.com/?post_type=recipe&#038;p=24462	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:31.556257	2014-01-14 18:55:31.556257	:</strong>\r\n1 package King Arthur Flour Gluten Free Cookie Mix\r\n1 egg\r\n2 tablespoons water\r\n1/2 cup unsalted butter, room temperature\r\n1/2 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips\r\n1/2 cup peanut butter chips\r\n1/2 cup mini marshmallows\r\n\r\n<a href="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/10810919355_d63f1bd8df_b.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-340" alt="10810919355_d63f1bd8df_b" src="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/10810919355_d63f1bd8df_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>
