r towel, wiping off excess oil.\r\n8. Cut puff pastry into strips that are  inch in width.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img alt="" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5509/10910944273_b655f4e725_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /> Photo by Sarah Stettin[/caption]\r\n\r\n9. Wrap puff pastry around asparagus, making sure not to overlap any pieces (wrap around about 3 times).\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img alt="" src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2817/10910667436_a74cac2e99_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /> Photo by Sarah Stettin[/caption]\r\n\r\n10. Beat 1 egg into a bowl and lightly brush the top of the puff pastry with egg wash. If you don't have a brush for the egg wash, just use a paper towel and lightly wipe the puff pastry with the beaten egg.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img alt="" src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2850/10910759534_c4375b408d_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /> Photo by Sarah Stettin[/caption]\r\n\r\n11. Place wrapped asparagus on cookie sheet and bake for about 15 minutes or until the puff pastry is golden brown.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img alt="" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7331/10910616525_1d4134202b_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /> Photo by Sarah Stettin[/caption]\r\n\r\n12. Remove from oven, arrange on your favorite serving dish, and bon appetit, you fancy pants you.	Puff Pastry Wrapped Asparagus 	http://spoonuniversity.com/?post_type=recipe&#038;p=25613	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:32.151949	2014-01-14 18:55:32.151949	:\r\n</b>1 bundle asparagus\r\n1 sheet puff pastry (thawed)\r\nOil\r\nSalt\r\n1 egg\r\n\r\n<b>
