t/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/ban2.jpg" width="633" height="1024" /></a> Photo by Leah Nordman[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>Mint Chip Hot Chocolate</strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients:\r\n</b>1 scoop mint chocolate chip ice cream\r\n1 tablespoon/packet instant hot chocolate\r\n\r\n<b>Directions:</b><b></b>\r\n1. Boil water.\r\n2. Add water to hot chocolate mix. Stir until combined.\r\n3. Add a scoop of mint chocolate chip ice cream and melt into heaven.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/10983120234_ee02cf70a6_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-401" alt="Photo by Leah Nordman" src="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/10983120234_ee02cf70a6_b.jpg" width="1024" height="681" /></a> Photo by Leah Nordman[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>Caramel Hot Chocolate</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n1 tablespoon caramel sauce\r\n1 pinch salt\r\n1 tablespoon/packet instant hot chocolate\r\n\r\n<b>Directions:</b><b></b>\r\n1. Boil water.\r\n2. While it boils, spoon the caramel sauce into the bottom of a mug.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="681"]<a href="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/10986070043_28ab236f0e_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-402" alt="Photo by Leah Nordman" src="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/10986070043_28ab236f0e_b.jpg" width="681" height="1024" /></a> Photo by Leah Nordman[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="681"]<a href="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/10986021894_33d20bbe4b_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-403" alt="Photo by Leah Nordman" src="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/10986021894_33d20bbe4b_b.jpg" width="681" height="1024" /></a> Photo by Leah Nordman[/caption]\r\n\r\n3. Add water and hot chocolate mix. Stir.\r\n4. Top with whipped cream, caramel sauce and a pinch of salt.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="681"]<a href="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/10985955396_239c466784_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-404" alt="Photo by Leah Nordham" src="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/10985955396_239c466784_b.jpg" width="681" height="1024" /></a> Photo by Leah Nordman[/caption]	5 Instant Hot Chocolate Upgrades	http://spoonuniversity.com/?post_type=recipe&#038;p=25884	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:32.246539	2014-01-14 18:55:32.246539	:</b>\r\n2 Reese's cups\r\n1 tablespoon/packet instant hot chocolate\r\n\r\n<b>
316	25972	Most people drink in college but the vast majority don't do so in a very "classy" way. After all, it's easy to fall back on old favorites - 40's, cheap wine and, if you're feeling fancy, some juice in your vodka. Our personal tastes are hardly to blame, as we don't have the time or money for complex cocktails. Yet every once in a while you want more. Maybe you're having friends over for dinner and need something with a little more oomph than a PBR. Or maybe you just want to pretend you're a real adult for a little. No matter what your reason, we are here to tell you that you don't have to shell out cash or effort to feel a little classier while drinking.\r\n<h2><strong>Wine Spritzer</strong></h2>\r\n"Wine spritzer" is a classy name for what could also be referred to as "ratchet champagne." You're essentially watering down wine for a cause. This makes this recipe extremely economical, as your wine will go twice as far. Remember that wine spritzers will always look classiest with a mason jar and lemon garnish.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/11/winespritzer3-1-1024x6781.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-4389" alt="Photo by Margaret Weinberg " src="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/11/winespritzer3-1-1024x6781.jpg" width="1024" height="678" /></a> Photo by Margaret Weinberg[/caption]\r\n\r\n[easy]\r\n\r\n<strong>Prep Time: </strong>2 minutes\r\n\r\n<strong>Servings:</strong>1\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:\r\n</strong>4 oz white wine\r\nSeltzer water\r\n1 slice of lemon\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:\r\n</strong>1. Fill your glass 2/3 of the way with white wine.\r\n\r\n2. Fill the rest of the glass with seltzer water.\r\n\r\n3. To garnish your drink, cut one thin, circular slice of lemon. Make a small slit at the bottom of the lemon slice and stick on the lip of your glass.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Tropical Fireball</strong></h2>\r\nIt is almost a fact that there is no one in the world who does not love Fireball (otherwise known as the cinnamon whisky drink of the Gods). It's easy to drink straight, but maybe you want to switch it up. Or perhaps you're having a tropical themed party. Either way, this is the drink for you.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/11/Fireball1-1-1024x8671.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-4390" alt="Photo by Margaret Weinberg" src="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/11/Fireball1-1-1024x8671.jpg" width="1024" height="867" /></a> Photo by Margaret Weinberg[/caption]\r\n\r\n[easy]\r\n\r\n<strong>Prep Time:</strong>4 minutes\r\n\r\n<strong>Servings:</strong>1\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:\r\n</strong>2 oz Fireball\r\n1/2 can of Cherry Pepsi\r\nLime\r\nMaraschino cherry\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:\r\n</strong>1. Pour one shot of Fireball into a glass. Fill the rest of the glass with Cherry Pepsi.\r\n\r\n2. Squeeze in the juice of one slice of lime. When done, skewer the lime slice and a maraschino cherry on a wooden skewer for some tropical flair.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>Black Tea Hot Toddy\r\n</strong></h2>\r\nThese hot toddies are great because they are literally spiked tea. Tea + alcohol = the best way to feel healthy and have fun at the same time. Invest in some cool mugs and surprise your guests at your next study party.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/11/hot-toddy1-1-1024x8821.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-4392" alt="Photo by Margaret Weinberg" src="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/11/hot-toddy1-1-1024x8821.jpg" width="1024" height="882" /></a> Photo by Margaret Weinberg[/caption]\r\n\r\n[medium]\r\n\r\n<strong>Prep Time:</strong>5 minutes\r\n\r\n<strong>Servings:</strong>1\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:\r\n</strong>2 oz bourbon\r\n1 black tea bag\r\nHot water\r\nHoney\r\nCinnamon\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions</strong>:\r\n1. Boil hot water and steep 1 black tea bag in a mug.\r\n\r\n2. Add one shot of bourbon and honey to taste. Sprinkle cinnamon over the top. Garnish with cinnamon sticks if you are really going for that decorative flair.\r\n<h2><strong>Bodega Bloody Mary</strong></h2>\r\nIn 2011 the American Chemical Societyspeculated that the Bloody Mary was the<a href="http://www.acs.org/content/acs/en/pressroom/newsreleases/2011/march/creating-the-perfect-bloody-mary-good-chemistry-of-fresh-ingredients.html"> "world's most complex cocktail."</a>But whoever told you that this infamous hangover cocktail had to contain everything from Worcestershire sauce to cayenne pepper was wrong. This stripped-down version only includes ingredients that can be found at your local bodega, while still making it look like you pulled out all the stops.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="612"]<a href="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/11/Bloody-mary1-1-612x10241.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-4394" alt="Photo by Margaret Weinberg " src="http://nyu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/7/2013/11/Bloody-mary1-1-612x10241.jpg" width="612" height="1024" /></a> Photo by Margaret Weinberg[/caption]\r\n\r\n[medium]\r\n\r\n<strong>Prep Time: </strong>5minutes\r\n\r\n<strong>Serving:</strong>1\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients\r\n</strong>40 oz malt liquor (preferably Olde English)\r\n2 oz vodka\r\n5 oz tomato juice\r\nLime\r\nSiracha\r\nCelery\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:\r\n</strong>1. Fill a glass halfway with malt liquor. Add the vodka and fill the glass the rest of the way with tomato juice.\r\n2. Squeeze the juice of half a lime into the drink and add siracha to taste.\r\n3. Garnish with celery.\r\n4. Drink the rest of your 40.\r\n<h2><strong>Grown Up Ice Cream Float</strong></h2>\r\nHave you ever wanted to eat an ice cream float