325	26600	If your go-to study snack is a banana and peanut butter, say hello to banana bread cupcakes with peanut butter frosting. Your simple snack can soon become a scrumptious dessert with the same two great flavors and serious procrastination power.\r\n\r\n[medium]\r\n\r\n<strong>Prep Time</strong>: 20 minutes\r\n<strong>Cook Time</strong>: 30 minutes\r\n<strong>Total Time</strong>: 50 minutes\r\n\r\n<strong>Servings</strong>: 16\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients for the cupcakes:</strong>\r\n3 ripe bananas\r\n2 eggs\r\n cup (1 stick) unsalted butter, softened\r\n1  cups flour\r\n cup granulated sugar\r\n1 teaspoon baking powder\r\n teaspoon baking soda\r\n teaspoon salt\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions for the cupcakes</strong>:\r\n1. Preheat the oven to 350F and line cupcake pan with cupcake papers.\r\n2. Mix together flour, granulated sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl. Set aside.\r\n3. Mash bananas in medium bowl until smooth.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/11050452796_ff4c4b1b69_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-436" alt="Photo by Christine Pritula " src="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/11050452796_ff4c4b1b69_b.jpg" width="1024" height="576" /></a> Photo by Christine Pritula[/caption]\r\n\r\n4. Lightly beat the eggs in small bowl.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img class=" wp-image-437" alt="11050362635_7e71be7fb2_b" src="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/11050362635_7e71be7fb2_b.jpg" width="1024" height="576" /> Photo by Christine Pritula[/caption]\r\n\r\n5. Combine butter, bananas and eggs with the dry ingredients. Mix until wet and dry ingredients are just incorporated.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/11050535663_e024c66d11_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-435" alt="Photo by Christine Pritula " src="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/11050535663_e024c66d11_b.jpg" width="1024" height="576" /></a> Photo by Christine Pritula[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/11050361555_3588c888a6_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-438" alt="Photo by Christine Pritula " src="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/11050361555_3588c888a6_b.jpg" width="1024" height="576" /></a> Photo by Christine Pritula[/caption]\r\n\r\n6. Spoon batter into cupcake holders untilabout  full.\r\n7. Bake for 30 minutes until golden brown.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/11050478334_f4aba13fbd_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-440" alt="Photo by Christine Pritula " src="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/11050478334_f4aba13fbd_b.jpg" width="1024" height="576" /></a> Photo by Christine Pritula[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients for the frosting</strong>:\r\n1 cup creamy peanut butter\r\n1 cup butter, softened\r\n3-4 cups powdered sugar\r\n1/3 cup milk\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions for the frosting</strong>:\r\n1. Whisk butter vigorously in a medium bowl until thick and fluffy.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a title="peanut butter banana cupcakes by WashU Spoon, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106291453@N07/11050478044/"><img alt="peanut butter banana cupcakes" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7426/11050478044_85e02f49a1_b.jpg" width="1024" height="576" /></a> Photo by Christine Pritula[/caption]\r\n\r\n2. Mix in peanut butter and whisk until smooth.\r\n3. Gradually alternate adding powdered sugar and milk while whisking until smooth.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/11050450426_e791d68197_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-439" alt="Photo by Christine Pritula " src="http://washu.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/12/2013/11/11050450426_e791d68197_b.jpg" width="1024" height="576" /></a> Photo by Christine Pritula[/caption]\r\n\r\n4. Spread or pipe the peanut butter frosting evenly on room temperature cupcakes.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a title="DSC00746 by WashU Spoon, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106291453@N07/11050349185/"><img alt="DSC00746" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7335/11050349185_2e705c71e3_b.jpg" width="1024" height="576" /></a> Photo by Christine Pritula[/caption]	Banana Bread Cupcakes with Peanut Butter Frosting	http://spoonuniversity.com/?post_type=recipe&#038;p=26600	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:32.669091	2014-01-14 18:55:32.669091	 for the cupcakes:</strong>\r\n3 ripe bananas\r\n2 eggs\r\n cup (1 stick) unsalted butter, softened\r\n1  cups flour\r\n cup granulated sugar\r\n1 teaspoon baking powder\r\n teaspoon baking soda\r\n teaspoon salt\r\n\r\n<strong>
