nt/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11199285005_9948ca533e_b.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11199285005_9948ca533e_b.jpg" width="682" height="487" /></a> Photo by Chloe Porter[/caption]\r\n\r\n9. Bake cookies for 10-12 minutes or until edges are slightly browned, rotating sheets halfway through.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_1726" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<a href="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11199305596_5d08832e7d_b.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-1726" alt="Photo by Chloe Porter" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11199305596_5d08832e7d_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /></a> Photo by Chloe Porter[/caption]\r\n\r\n10. Cool for one minute on baking sheet, then transfer cookies to wire rack to cool thoroughly.	Day 5: Salted Oatmeal Chocolate Chip Cookies	http://spoonuniversity.com/?post_type=recipe&#038;p=27434	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:33.079873	2014-01-14 18:55:33.079873	:</strong>\r\n\r\n1 cup flour\r\n1 teaspoon baking powder\r\nteaspoon salt\r\nteaspoon baking soda\r\n1 stick unsalted butter, room temperature\r\ncup packed light brown sugar\r\ncup sugar\r\n1 egg, room temperature\r\n2 teaspoons vanilla extract\r\n2 cups old fashioned rolled oats\r\n1 cup dark chocolate chips\r\nFlaky sea salt (like Maldon)\r\n\r\n<strong>
