ilkins[/caption]\r\n\r\n6. Gradually incorporate dry ingredients from step 3 into wet ingredients from step 4.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img alt="" src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2819/11279667473_746d81ba55_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /> Photo by Abigail Wilkins[/caption]\r\n\r\n7. Fold in the cooled chocolate.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img alt="" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5543/11279583546_595e5ab68d_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /> Photo by Abigail Wilkins[/caption]\r\n\r\n8. Stir in the chopped Andes mint pieces.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img alt="" src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3769/11279605014_1f383c7003_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /> Photo by Abigail Wilkins[/caption]\r\n\r\n9. Chill dough in refrigerator for 10 minutes before scooping onto cookie sheet.\r\n10. Scoop 9 dough mounds onto cookie sheet, spacing evenly (mounds should be about 1.5 inches in diameter).\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img alt="" src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2855/11279596516_de2995c468_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /> Photo by Abigail Wilkins[/caption]\r\n\r\n11. Bake cookies for 10 minutes.\r\n12. Reverse the shelves that the baking sheets are on, and bake for about 9 to 10 more minutes until the tops of the cookies are dry looking with some small cracks.\r\n13. Cool cookies completely on the sheets before removing, and enjoy!\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1024"]<img alt="" src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3711/11279680313_0780387f4a_b.jpg" width="1024" height="683" /> Photo by Abigail Wilkins[/caption]	Double Chocolate Mint Cookies	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/double-chocolate-mint-cookies/	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:34.338704	2014-01-14 18:55:34.338704	:\r\n</b>6 ounces semisweet or bittersweet (60-percent) chocolate chips\r\n2 tablespoons unsalted butter\r\n1 cup flour\r\n2 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa\r\n1 teaspoon baki