349	27518	One thing that I always look forward to when I go home is the fresh blueberry cake made from my grandmother's family recipe. Each time I have it Im reminded of lazy Sunday afternoons, when I would sit down with a slice of cake, a cup of milk and a great book. It is a fairly straightforward recipe and can be used with either fresh or thawed frozen blueberries, which helps to incorporate more fruit into our lives during these cold winter months.\r\n\r\n[easy]\r\n\r\n<strong>Prep Time:</strong> 15 minutes\r\n<strong>Cooking Time:</strong> 30 minutes\r\n<strong>Total Time:</strong> 45 minutes\r\n<strong>Servings:</strong> 9\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n\r\n cup butter, softened\r\n1 egg, well beaten\r\n cup + 1 tablespoon sugar\r\n teaspoon vanilla extract\r\n cup milk\r\n1 1/3 cup + 2 tablespoons flour\r\n2 teaspoons baking powder\r\n cup blueberries, divided\r\n1 teaspoon cinnamon\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="Blueberry Cake Image 1 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11159189313/"><img alt="Blueberry Cake Image 1" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7445/11159189313_a741cf5aec_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Clark Halpern[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Preheat the oven to 350F.\r\n2. Mix the softened butter with the egg and  cup sugar until the mixture has a uniform consistency.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="Blueberry Cake Image 2 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11159010395/"><img alt="Blueberry Cake Image 2" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5531/11159010395_48e7a92c96_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Clark Halpern[/caption]\r\n\r\n3. Add the vanilla extract and milk, beat well.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="Blueberry Cake 3 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11159189123/"><img alt="Blueberry Cake 3" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7431/11159189123_a6865e05ab_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Clark Halpern[/caption]\r\n\r\n4. Slowly add 1 1/3 cup flour and baking powder, beating thoroughly.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="Blueberry Cake 4 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11159070314/"><img alt="Blueberry Cake 4" src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3792/11159070314_5d32e3ef9d_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Clark Halpern[/caption]\r\n\r\n5. Fold half of the blueberries into the batter.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="Blueberry Cake 5 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11159070294/"><img alt="Blueberry Cake 5" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7389/11159070294_e532b123d3_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Clark Halpern[/caption]\r\n\r\n6. Add the batter into a greased 9x9 pan.\r\n7. Coat the remaining blueberries with the 2 tablespoons of flour, then layer on top of the batter in the pan.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="Blueberry Cake 6 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11159070244/"><img alt="Blueberry Cake 6" src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3773/11159070244_172e97ee6b_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Clark Halpern[/caption]\r\n\r\n8. Combine the cinnamon and remaining sugar and apply in a thin layer over the cake.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="Blueberry Cake 7 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11159010155/"><img alt="Blueberry Cake 7" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7355/11159010155_bd57b6643b_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Clark Halpern[/caption]\r\n\r\n9. Bake for approximately 30 minutes until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean.\r\n10. Allow to cool slightly, and enjoy.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="Blueberry cake 9 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11159188803/"><img alt="Blueberry cake 9" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7347/11159188803_bd380fc8ee_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Clark Halpern[/caption]	Blueberry Cake	http://spoonuniversity.com/?post_type=recipe&#038;p=27518	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:33.117549	2014-01-14 18:55:33.117549	:</strong>\r\n\r\n cup butter, softened\r\n1 egg, well beaten\r\n cup + 1 tablespoon sugar\r\n teaspoon vanilla extract\r\n cup milk\r\n1 1/3 cup + 2 tablespoons flour\r\n2 teaspoons baking powder\r\n cup blueberries, divided\r\n1 teaspoon cinnamon\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="Blueberry Cake Image 1 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11159189313/"><img alt="Blueberry Cake Image 1" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7445/11159189313_a741cf5aec_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Clark Halpern[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>
