ogether flour, cream of tartar, baking soda, salt and pumpkin pie spice in a large bowl.\r\n3. With an electric hand mixer, blend the sugar and softened butter together until fluffy.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1000"]<a href="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/IMG_3485.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-1910" alt="Photo by Vinita Saggurti" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/IMG_3485.jpg" width="1000" height="750" /></a> Photo by Vinita Saggurti[/caption]\r\n\r\n4. Add egg and beat for about 30 seconds.\r\n5. Add pumpkin pure until combined.\r\n6. Add the dry ingredients at a low speed until all ingredients are mixed together.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="1000"]<a href="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/IMG_3491.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-1911" alt="Photo by Vinita Saggurti" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/IMG_3491.jpg" width="1000" height="750" /></a> Photo by Vinita Saggurti[/caption]\r\n\r\n7. Mix together the cinnamon and sugar in a small bowl.\r\n8. Roll heaping tablespoons of dough into a ball and cover in cinnamon sugar.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="700"]<a href="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11470092035_38999471ed_c.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-1915" alt="Photo by Vinita Saggurti" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11470092035_38999471ed_c.jpg" width="700" height="525" /></a> Photo by Vinita Saggurti[/caption]\r\n\r\n9. Bake for 10-12 minutes, until puffy and golden.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a href="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/IMG_3505.jpg"><img class=" wp-image-1923 " alt="Photo by Vinita Saggurti" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites