384	29434	Theres a reason why the best desserts are a balance of savory and sweet and this recipe echoes this sentiment. Just as you were getting bored of ordinary chocolate chip cookies, this recipe brings together Nutella and coarse sea salt, a taste combination that elevates your palette. Fit for a party, study break or snack, these Nutella-stuffed chocolate chip cookies will revamp your understanding of an old classic. And the best part about this baking process is the aroma of the browned butter. Tip: The more browning the better! The more browning, the more developed flavors you will get.\r\n\r\n[medium]\r\n\r\n<strong>Prep time:</strong> 45 minutes to 1 hour\r\n<strong>Cook time:</strong> 15 to 20 minutes or until edges turn golden brown (cook time will increase proportionally if cookies are larger)\r\n<strong>Total time:</strong> 1 hour to 1 hour 20 minute\r\n<strong>Servings:</strong> 16 large cookies\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n\r\n2  cups all purpose flour\r\n1  teaspoon baking soda\r\n teaspoon salt\r\n1 cup (2 sticks) unsalted butter at room temperature\r\n1  cup packed dark brown sugar\r\n cup granulated sugar\r\n1 large egg and 1 large egg yolk\r\n1  teaspoon vanilla extract\r\n1 tablespoon plain Greek yogurt\r\n cup semi-sweet chocolate chips\r\n cup milk chocolate chips\r\n cup dark chocolate chips\r\n1 jar of Nutella, chilled in the freezer for  hour\r\nCoarse sea salt for sprinkling\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies1 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11378066123/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies1" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7454/11378066123_53641b51a7_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>Instructions:</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Mix flour, baking soda and salt in a large bowl until combined and set aside.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies2 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11378066893/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies2" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5548/11378066893_0b82725f12_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n2. Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat. Eventually, the butter will start to foam. Whisk consistently throughout this process.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies3 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11378066273/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies3" src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2886/11378066273_f6f06b3580_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies5 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377941376/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies5" src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3669/11377941376_5d77c2ebda_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n3. After about 5-10 minutes, the butter will begin to brown at the bottom of the saucepan. Continue to whisk and remove the pan from heat when it begins to brown. Transfer the butter to a large bowl to prevent burning and set aside to cool.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies6 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11378066903/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies6" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7439/11378066903_e050923bd1_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n4. With a mixer, beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.\r\n5. Beat in the egg and egg yolk (one at a time) and then vanilla and yogurt simultaneously until incorporated.\r\n6. Gradually add the dry ingredients from step 2 to the mixture until smooth.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies14 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377986054/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies14" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7309/11377986054_5c05efd071_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n7. Gently fold in all of the chocolate chips.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies15 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377942716/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies15" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7420/11377942716_9784e4b1b1_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n8. Preheat the oven to 350F.Chill dough and Nutella in the freezer for  hour.\r\n9. Roll 1  tablespoon of dough into a ball and flatten it very thinly onto a buttered cookie sheet. Continue to do this with the remaining dough and place the dough circles inches apart from each other.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies16 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377932105/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies16" src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3729/11377932105_e1bbb8a1c1_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n10. Place  tablespoon of chilled Nutella in the middle of half of all the flattened dough balls.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies17 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377932265/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies17" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7417/11377932265_f6867874fd_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n11. Place a circle of cookie dough on top of a dough circle with Nutella in order to make a sandwich. Crimp edges to seal.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies18 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377943316/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies18" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7367/11377943316_9d4e9107db_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n12. Bake for 15-20 minutes or until edges turn golden brown.\r\n13. Sprinkle with sea salt and let cool on wire racks.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies21 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377932885/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies21" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7370/11377932885_e98fd90995_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]	Nutella-Stuffed Chocolate Chip Cookies	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/nutella-stuffed-chocolate-chip-cookies/	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:34.235645	2014-01-14 18:55:34.235645	:</strong>\r\n\r\n2  cups all purpose flour\r\n1  teaspoon baking soda\r\n teaspoon salt\r\n1 cup (2 sticks) unsalted butter at room temperature\r\n1  cup packed dark brown sugar\r\n cup granulated sugar\r\n1 large egg and 1 large egg yolk\r\n1  teaspoon vanilla extract\r\n1 tablespoon plain Greek yogurt\r\n cup semi-sweet chocolate chips\r\n cup milk chocolate chips\r\n cup dark chocolate chips\r\n1 jar of Nutella, chilled in the freezer for  hour\r\nCoarse sea salt for sprinkling\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies1 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11378066123/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies1" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7454/11378066123_53641b51a7_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>Instructions:</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Mix flour, baking soda and salt in a large bowl until combined and set aside.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies2 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11378066893/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies2" src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5548/11378066893_0b82725f12_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n2. Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat. Eventually, the butter will start to foam. Whisk consistently throughout this process.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies3 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11378066273/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies3" src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2886/11378066273_f6f06b3580_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies5 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377941376/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies5" src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3669/11377941376_5d77c2ebda_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n3. After about 5-10 minutes, the butter will begin to brown at the bottom of the saucepan. Continue to whisk and remove the pan from heat when it begins to brown. Transfer the butter to a large bowl to prevent burning and set aside to cool.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies6 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11378066903/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies6" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7439/11378066903_e050923bd1_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n4. With a mixer, beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.\r\n5. Beat in the egg and egg yolk (one at a time) and then vanilla and yogurt simultaneously until incorporated.\r\n6. Gradually add the dry ingredients from step 2 to the mixture until smooth.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies14 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377986054/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies14" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7309/11377986054_5c05efd071_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n7. Gently fold in all of the chocolate chips.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies15 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377942716/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies15" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7420/11377942716_9784e4b1b1_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n8. Preheat the oven to 350F.Chill dough and Nutella in the freezer for  hour.\r\n9. Roll 1  tablespoon of dough into a ball and flatten it very thinly onto a buttered cookie sheet. Continue to do this with the remaining dough and place the dough circles inches apart from each other.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies16 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377932105/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies16" src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3729/11377932105_e1bbb8a1c1_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n10. Place  tablespoon of chilled Nutella in the middle of half of all the flattened dough balls.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies17 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377932265/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies17" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7417/11377932265_f6867874fd_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n11. Place a circle of cookie dough on top of a dough circle with Nutella in order to make a sandwich. Crimp edges to seal.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies18 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377943316/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies18" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7367/11377943316_9d4e9107db_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n12. Bake for 15-20 minutes or until edges turn golden brown.\r\n13. Sprinkle with sea salt and let cool on wire racks.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogNutellaCookies21 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11377932885/"><img alt="FogNutellaCookies21" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7370/11377932885_e98fd90995_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]
385	29436	What's better than warming yourself up on a frigid winter day with a steaming cup of rich, thick hot chocolate? Probably nothing. That's why these "hot chocolate" cookies, a mix of your favorite drink with classic chocolate chip cookies, are the perfect winter treat. By using hot chocolate mix instead of cocoa powder and adding toasted marshmallows, each cookie becomes a warm, chocolately, gooey, treat. My only advice: if you choose to toast the marshmallows, make sure to watch them cook the whole time (I may or may not have almost blown up my toaster oven).\r\n\r\n[easy]\r\n\r\n<strong>Prep Time:</strong> 10 to 15 minutes\r\n<strong>Cook Time:</strong> 10 to 12 minutes\r\n<strong>Total Time:</strong>20 to 27 minutes\r\n\r\n<strong>Servings:</strong>2 or 3 dozen cookies\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n\r\n2 cups flour\r\n1 cup good hot chocolate mix (I used Jacques Torres)\r\n1 teaspoon salt\r\n2 teaspoon baking soda\r\n2 sticks butter, softened\r\n cup granulated sugar\r\n cup packed brown sugar\r\n2 large eggs\r\n2 teaspoons vanilla\r\n1  cups semi-sweet chocolate chips\r\n1 cup marshmallows (toasting optional)\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Preheat oven to 350F.\r\n\r\n2. Toast marshmallows in toaster oven on a sheet of tinfoil. Watch carefully!\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="640"]<a href="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485472273_14a2daafee_z.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-1936" alt="Photo by Gabby Manoff" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485472273_14a2daafee_z.jpg" width="640" height="427" /></a> Photo by Gabby Manoff[/caption]\r\n\r\n3. Combine flour, hot chocolate mix, salt, and baking soda in a separate bowl.\r\n\r\n4. In a big bowl, cream together the butter and two types of sugar.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="640"]<a href="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485373454_0f6ec30b2a_z-1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-1938" alt="Photo by Gabby Manoff" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485373454_0f6ec30b2a_z-1.jpg" width="640" height="427" /></a> Photo by Gabby Manoff[/caption]\r\n\r\n5. Add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla. Beat well.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="640"]<a href="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485491994_4c51b3b6c5_z.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-1939" alt="Photo by Gabby Manoff" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485491994_4c51b3b6c5_z.jpg" width="640" height="427" /></a> Photo by Gabby Manoff[/caption]\r\n\r\n6.Slowly add the flour and hot chocolate mixture to the butter and sugar mixture. Mix until combined.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="427"]<a href="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485370724_f6c5c21c02_z.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-1940" alt="Photo by Gabby Manoff" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485370724_f6c5c21c02_z.jpg" width="427" height="640" /></a> Photo by Gabby Manoff[/caption]\r\n\r\n7. Mix in chocolate chips and toasted marshmallows.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="640"]<a href="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485451426_68fb2a6cbc_z.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-1941" alt="Photo by Gabby Manoff" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485451426_68fb2a6cbc_z.jpg" width="640" height="427" /></a> Photo by Gabby Manoff[/caption]\r\n\r\n8. Drop two tablespoons of cookie dough onto cookie sheets and bake for 9-12 minutes.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="640"]<a href="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485450216_f2fc827c7b_z.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-1942" alt="Photo by Gabby Manoff" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485450216_f2fc827c7b_z.jpg" width="640" height="427" /></a> Photo by Gabby Manoff[/caption]\r\n\r\n9. Let cool and enjoy...they will probably be gone sooner than you think!\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="640"]<a href="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485449446_aea2c953b8_z.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-1943" alt="Photo by Gabby Manoff" src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11485449446_aea2c953b8_z.jpg" width="640" height="427" /></a> Photo by Gabby Manoff[/caption]	Day 24: Hot Chocolate Cookies	http://spoonuniversity.com/?post_type=recipe&#038;p=29436	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:34.238123	2014-01-14 18:55:34.238123	:</strong>\r\n\r\n2 cups flour\r\n1 cup good hot chocolate mix (I used Jacques Torres)\r\n1 teaspoon salt\r\n2 teaspoon baking soda\r\n2 sticks butter, softened\r\n cup granulated sugar\r\n cup packed brown sugar\r\n2 large eggs\r\n2 teaspoons vanilla\r\n1  cups semi-sweet chocolate chips\r\n1 cup marshmallows (toasting optional)\r\n\r\n<strong>
