t/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11506171073_d577724e3a_c.jpg"><img src="http://upenn.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2013/12/11506171073_d577724e3a_c.jpg" alt="Photo by Chloe Porter" width="700" height="525" class="size-full wp-image-1963" /></a> Photo by Chloe Porter[/caption]\r\n\r\n5. Bake for about 10 minutes, or until the edges start to set. Let cool.\r\n	Day 23: Nutella Chocolate Chunk Walnut Cookies	http://spoonuniversity.com/recipe/day-23-nutella-chocolate-chunk-walnut-cookies/	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:34.258903	2014-01-14 18:55:34.258903	:\r\n</strong>1 cup all-purpose flour\r\n2 eggs\r\n cup Nutella\r\n cup sugar\r\n cup chopped walnuts\r\n cup dark chocolate chunks\r\n\r\n<strong>
387	29523	This cheery cookie is sure to put anyone in the Christmas spirit. This recipe allows you to turn a simple heart shaped cookie into jolly old St. Nicholas, which will bring a smile to anyones face. Wow your family with these cookies at your Christmas feast or give them to a friend as a festive present.\r\n\r\n[medium]\r\n\r\n<strong>Prep time: </strong>20minutes\r\n<strong>Cook time:</strong>6-7 minutes\r\n<strong>Total time:</strong>Around 30 minutes\r\n\r\n<strong>Servings:</strong>24 cookies\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n<strong></strong>1 cup butter\r\n1 cup sugar\r\n1 large egg\r\n1 teaspoon vanilla\r\n2 teaspoon baking powder\r\n3 cups flour\r\n24 Red Hots\r\n24 marshmallows\r\nHeart shaped cookie cutter\r\nMini chocolate chips\r\nVanilla frosting\r\nRed food coloring\r\nEdible white glitter flakes\r\n\r\n<strong>Instructions:</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Preheat oven to 350F.\r\n\r\n2. In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar with an electric mixer. Beat in egg and vanilla. Add baking powder and flour one cup at a time, mixing after each addition. The dough will be very firm. Do not chill dough.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="aligncenter" width="800"]<a href="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521542114_61b50386d6_c.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-741" alt="Photo by Isabelle Langheim" src="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521542114_61b50386d6_c.jpg" width="800" height="532" /></a> Photo by Isabelle Langheim[/caption]\r\n\r\n2. Take about an eighth of the dough out of the mixer and roll it out with a rolling pin on a floured surface. Roll the dough to be about  inch thick, dough should be only slightly thinner than the cutter, and cut with the heart shaped cookie cutter.\r\n\r\nHINT: Flour both the rolling pin and counter generously to keep the dough from sticking to either.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="aligncenter" width="800"]<a href="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521602706_8c6a1f95eb_c.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-742" alt="Photo by Isabelle Langheim" src="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521602706_8c6a1f95eb_c.jpg" width="800" height="532" /></a> Photo by Isabelle Langheim[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="aligncenter" width="800"]<a href="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521604576_7dcbf01d78_c.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-743" alt="Photo by Isabelle Langheim" src="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521604576_7dcbf01d78_c.jpg" width="800" height="532" /></a> Photo by Isabelle Langheim[/caption]\r\n\r\n3. Place the cut dough on an ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="aligncenter" width="800"]<a href="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521611686_5cbea24897_c.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-744" alt="Photo by Isabelle Langheim" src="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521611686_5cbea24897_c.jpg" width="800" height="532" /></a> Photo by Isabelle Langheim[/caption]\r\n\r\n4. Bake 6 to 7 minutes or until cookies are slightly browned. Remove from sheet immediately and place cookies on a wire rack to cool.\r\n\r\n5. Once fully cooled, take  cup of vanilla frosting and make it red using a few drops of red food coloring. The pointed part of the heart is the top of the cookie and will be Santas hat. Use a knife to add the frosting hat.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="aligncenter" width="800"]<a href="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521548614_0017f05705_c.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-745" alt="Photo by Isabelle Langheim" src="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521548614_0017f05705_c.jpg" width="800" height="532" /></a> Photo by Isabelle Langheim[/caption]\r\n\r\n6. To make his beard, swirl vanilla frosting at the bottom of the cookie, leaving space between the red hat and the cheeks.\r\n\r\n7. Add a half a drop of red food coloring to  cup vanilla frosting to create pink frosting to make rosy cheeks for the Santa.\r\n\r\n8. Add the edible white glitter flakes to the beard.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="aligncenter" width="800"]<a href="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521550474_fc567434a3_c.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-746" alt="Photo by Isabelle Langheim" src="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521550474_fc567434a3_c.jpg" width="800" height="532" /></a> Photo by Isabelle Langheim[/caption]\r\n\r\n9. Make your own pastry bag by taking a plastic baggie and cutting a small hole at one of the bottom corners. Add white frosting to trim the hat.\r\n\r\n10. Add a Red Hot for the nose, two mini chocolate chips for the eyes and a marshmallow for the top of the hat.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_" align="alignnone" width="800"]<a href="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521533235_cfc063c178_c1.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-757" alt="11521533235_cfc063c178_c" src="http://uiuc.spoonuniversity.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/12/11521533235_cfc063c178_c1.jpg" width="800" height="532" /></a> Photo by Isabelle Langheim[/caption]	Santa Baby Sugar Cookies	http://spoonuniversity.com/?post_type=recipe&#038;p=29523	\N	2014-01-14 18:55:34.277347	2014-01-14 18:55:34.277347	:</strong>\r\n<strong></strong>1 cup butter\r\n1 cup sugar\r\n1 large egg\r\n1 teaspoon vanilla\r\n2 teaspoon baking powder\r\n3 cups flour\r\n24 Red Hots\r\n24 marshmallows\r\nHeart shaped cookie cutter\r\nMini chocolate chips\r\nVanilla frosting\r\nRed food coloring\r\nEdible white glitter flakes\r\n\r\n<strong>Instructions:</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Preheat oven to 350F.\r\n\r\n2. In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar with an electric mixer. 