390	29775	The holidays are undoubtedly the best time of year and nothing says celebration quite like eggnog. Traditionally served on Christmas, this classic should not just be solely reserved as a wintertime treat or in the form of a drink. Ideal for those who like to reinvent classics, this eggnog bread is light but still packs a punch with its rum-flavored accent.\r\n\r\n[medium]\r\n\r\n<strong>Prep time:</strong> 20 minutes\r\n<strong>Cook time</strong>: 40-60 minutes for 9x5 inch loaf pan or 35-40 minutes for three 3x5 inch loaf pans\r\n<strong>Total time:</strong>1 hr\r\n<strong>Servings:</strong> 12\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n\r\n2 eggs, beaten\r\n1 cup eggnog\r\n2 teaspoons rum-flavored extract\r\n1 cup white sugar\r\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\r\n cup (1 stick) butter softened at room temperature\r\n2  cups all-purpose flour\r\n2 teaspoons baking powder\r\n teaspoon salt\r\n teaspoon ground nutmeg\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogBread2 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11612385294/"><img alt="FogBread2" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7309/11612385294_99f177d692_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Preheat oven to 350F. Grease 9x5 inch loaf pan or three 3x5 inch loaf pans with butter.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogBread3 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11612259723/"><img alt="FogBread3" src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7398/11612259723_dcbcd5272d_b.jpg" width="770" height="500" /></a> Photo by Mei Lan Fogarty[/caption]\r\n\r\n2. Blend together the eggs in a mixer.\r\n3. Mix in eggnog, rum extract, sugar, vanilla and butter.\r\n\r\n[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="770"]<a title="FogBread6 by uchi.spoonuniversity, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/106796684@N05/11612052015/